metadata.metaValue: I don't know why I need to do this. It's the method to convert to horizontal FOV.

Add the array of flags to indicate which components are in the set.

This array should be the same size as the topo component that is being
targetted. For example, if target=point_component, and the passed-in
object has 8 points, and only the first two should be in the set,
use a bitset of {1,1,0,0,0,0,0,0}

Indicate which geo property this set is targetting.
Most of the time this will be one of the topological
components, like "point_component", "face_component", etc
